page.title: 11CARNIVAL
page.content: THE CARNIVAL IS HELD EACH YEAR IN JUNE. A PARADE GOES SLOWLY THROUGH BOZEAT AND FINISHES AT THE PLAYING FIELDS. THE CARNIVAL STARTED THIS YEAR AT 2o'CLOCK.THERE WERE FLOATS AND PEOPLE DRESSED UP IN PUNK OUTFITS,AND SOME MEN WERE DRESSED AS OLD WOMEN AND COLLECTED MONEY. THERE WERE LOTS OF STALLS AT THE PLAYING FIELDS.YOU COULD WIN GOLDFISH, FLUFFY TOYSAND MANY OTHER THINGS. AT ABOUT 3o'CLOCK,THE MAJORETTES WERE IN THE MIDDLE OF THE FIELD.AFTER THAT THERE WAS A DOG SHOW,AND THEN A DISPLAY OF JUDO.THE WINNING FLOAT WAS FROM CLAYLAND CLOSE.THE THEME WAS"THE OLD WOMAN WHO LIVED IN A SHOE".THEY WON 5 POUNDS AND A CUP. THIS YEAR'S CARNIVAL QUEEN WAS TARA HOLMES WHO IS 15 YEARS OLD.
